President Trump and First Lady Melania Trump extend their greetings and appreciation for the brave men and women of the Armed Forces on Super Bowl Sunday. They acknowledge that many service members are unable to be home with family and friends and express gratitude for their sacrifice in defending liberty and the American way of life. The Trumps hold them in their hearts and thank them for their freedom as they proudly stand for the National Anthem. They send their best wishes for an enjoyable Super Bowl Sunday and pray for God's blessings and protection on the troops and the United States.